<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=aubrey17&buddyTimeStamp=20060403&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fprocess_buddy.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193059732&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Abby</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Abby lives at <a href='/home/?user=aubrey17'>19792 Rosewood Road</a> in one of the beautiful, historic homes of Ravenwood.  Though she'd like to preserve the antique style of her house, Abby has been hard at work fixing the place up since she moved to Millsberry on May 8, 2005.<br><br>Abby is truly a multitalented person.  She has an exciting, creative flair that can easily be seen in every aspect of her life, from her stylish zebra-patterned clothing to her dramatic violet-painted bedroom and the art she creates in brilliant shades of pink.  One of Abby's favorite ways of expressing herself is with painting.  She'll spend hours at a time filling canvases, sheets of paper, and even walls with bright, colorful paintings.  <br><br>As she paints, Abby often listens to music (which is another one of her favorite hobbies) for inspiration.  While she loves listening to a wide variety of tunes, Abby also enjoys creating her own music!  The styles of music Abby likes best are pop, rap, and classic rock.  She says that she likes the upbeat quality of pop, the quick rhythms of rap, and the innovative lyrics of classic rock.  When she writes her own music, Abby often tries to combine her favorite aspects from each of these three types of music.<br><br>One of Abby's other interests has influenced both her painting and her music - that would be her favorite subject at school, math.  Abby always looks forward to her math class at <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/academy">Millsberry Academy</a>.  She enjoys looking for patterns in the numbers and using logic to solve complex problems.  Math has also helped her understand the geometry behind the concept of perspective in painting, so her paintings look very realistic and well designed.<br><br>When she wants to relax, Abby usually heads over to her best friend's house.  They often spend the afternoon listening to music and talking about what's happening around town.  Sometimes, they'll drop by the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/theater.phtml">theater</a> at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/">Downtown Entertainment Complex</a> to see if there are any new movies playing.  When the weather is sunny, Abby also likes to watch soccer games in <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a>.  If you're ever in the stands at a soccer game, keep an eye out for Abby; she'll be the one cheering her team on the loudest!<br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Abby, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
